[ProMED-mail is very grateful to Dr Kaba and his co-authors from Serbia, Germany, and Romania for the firsthand information above.

We are informed that the serological tests on Serbian cattle described above were performed in the Laboratory of Veterinary Epidemiology and Economics, Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, Warsaw University of Life Sciences-SGGW, Warsaw, Poland.

Suspected SBV infections were reported by ProMED-mail from Hungary and Slovenia in January 2013; confirmation or otherwise was requested in postings 20130106.1484643 and 20130126.1516151, respectively. No response from the said countries has become available so far; hence, the RFI is being hereby repeated. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Serbia can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/1BX*. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

