[A map of Europe can be accessed at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/europe_map.htm. A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the UK can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/7l4v; for the location of Aberdeenshire, Scotland, see map at http://tinyurl.com/kos6cv7.

According to the SBV page of the Friedrich-Loeffler-Institut (FLI) in Germany, last updated 11 Jun 2013, "so far infections with Schmallenberg virus have been detected in the following (17) European countries: Germany, Netherlands, Belgium, UK and Northern Ireland, France, Italy, Luxembourg, Spain, Denmark, Estonia, Ireland, Norway, Sweden, Finland, Poland, Austria, and Switzerland. According to unconfirmed reports, there could be infections in additional European countries."

The Serbian Republic can now be added to the 17 countries above; information from other countries, and in particular from Hungary and Slovenia, is anticipated. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/7l4v.]
